The gram-positive bacilli with a bamboo stick appearance and large, gray, non-hemolytic colonies with irregular borders are also characteristic of Bacillus anthracis. Brucellosis typically presents with fever, malaise, and joint pain. Listeriosis presents with fever, muscle aches, and sometimes gastrointestinal symptoms. Tularemia presents with fever, chills, and swollen lymph nodes.
